    "summary": "Specializing in infrastructure public-private partnerships, Matt offers a unique diversity of perspectives as developer, investor, government adviser, private sector adviser and banker. Having successfully closed major PPP (P3) transactions from both public and private sides of the table, he understands the motivations and limitations of the other parties and knows what it takes to sustainably deliver major infrastructure projects for the public good.\n\nWell-versed in the following:\n* PPP/P3 transaction advisory\n* Capacity building and institutional strengthening in emerging markets\n* International project finance (capital markets/municipal finance/Private Activity Bonds, TIFIA, bank financing, equity investment, development partner funding, financial modelling; structuring and documentation)\n* PPP/P3 bid management and capital raising for equity developers\n* Proposal evaluation and due diligence expertise, including handling of unsolicited proposals\n* Commercial contracting (comprehensive project agreements, risk allocation)\n* Project prioritization and procurement (feasibility analysis, value for money, RFQ and RFP development, government approvals, bidder evaluation and selection, commercial and financial closing)\n* Political and stakeholder engagement",
